Introduction

We Girls (also stylized as WeGirls) was a girl group under Aftermoon Entertainment. Originally with eight members, they debuted on August 31, 2018, with the single album "On Air". After months of inactivity since 2021, the group presumably disbanded in early 2022. In February 2022, Yehana revealed in an Instagram DM with a fan that We Girls had disbanded.
